The paper introduces a generic framework for interactive learning, which is a topic that falls under the umbrella of machine learning. The specific focus is on interactive structure discovery, which involves identifying the underlying structure of a dataset through a series of interactive queries. This could be applied to a variety of domains, such as active learning, top-k item identification, and drug discovery. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Additionally, the paper mentions information retrieval (IR) and database (DB) applications, so those sub-categories are also possible.
